Rob: this usually happens because resources are allocated (e.g. colors, fonts, images) but not disposed.  To avoid this always use TaskListColorsAndFonts which handles disposing colors and only creates one per workbench instance.  For now I've commented out the following line from AbstractRepositoryTaskEditor, so you may want to check if that messed up a color.  Please double-check that you're not assign those resources anywhere else.

	viewer.getControl().setBackground(new Color(expandableComposite.getDisplay(), 123, 34, 155));

Meghan: if you could double check that this doesn't recur with the next dev build that would be great.  Fyi, you can also mark hits read via the context menu's Mark -> Read.
